  "text": "where S l×l , U l×h and V h×h denote the sensor-sensor, sensor-anchor, respectively anchor-anchor measurements, and D is a diagonal matrix with D ii = n j=1 |Z ij |. Note that V is a matrix with all nonzero entries, since the (correct) measurement between any two anchors is readily available, and the vector (U a) l×1 can be interpreted as the anchor contribution in the estimation of the sensors. Since a T (D V − V )a is a (nonnegative) constant, we are interested in minimizing the integer quadratic form z T (D S − S)z − 2z T U a. Unfortunately, the non-convex constraint z ∈ Z l 2 renders the problem NP-hard, and thus we introduce the relaxation to a quadratically constrained quadratic program (QCQP) from equation (9.2), whose solution can be shown to be z * = (D S − S + λI) −1 (U a) [CITATION_1] . S z yields the optimization problem shown in (9.3), which is very similar to the one in (9.2).",
